.TH "stm32_adc_debugfs_reg_access" 9 "stm32_adc_debugfs_reg_access" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
stm32_adc_debugfs_reg_access \- read or write register value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" stm32_adc_debugfs_reg_access
.BI "(struct iio_dev *indio_dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned reg "  ","
.BI "unsigned writeval "  ","
.BI "unsigned *readval "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "indio_dev" 12
IIO device structure
.IP "reg" 12
register offset
.IP "writeval" 12
value to write
.IP "readval" 12
value to read
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
To read a value from an ADC register:
echo [ADC reg offset] > direct_reg_access
cat direct_reg_access

To write a value in a ADC register:
echo [ADC_reg_offset] [value] > direct_reg_access
